[1;34m## [0m[1;34mPurpose[0m

The Centaur Manifest exists for one reason: to let
a small human unit move at machine speed without
losing coherence.

In the centaur era, execution is cheap. Drafting,
scaffolding, refactoring, exploration, and even
broad solution search can be delegated to capable
agents. The limiting factors shift. The hard work
becomes maintaining shared intent, bounding risk,
proving correctness, integrating safely, and
learning fast enough to steer.

This document is self-contained. It defines tenets
and a recommended way of working that makes those
tenets second nature.

[1;34m## [0m[1;34mScope and relationship to organization-level[0m
   [1;34mframeworks[0m

This manifest is intentionally [3m[34munit-scale[0m: it is
optimized for 2â€“4 humans shipping and learning
fast with AI augmentation.

In many organizations, there is also a
portfolio/coordination layer whose job is to align
multiple teams, allocate attention across
competing outcomes, and keep a consistent
north-star focus under dependencies and politics.
Frameworks like [1m[1;37mOBAF[0m are built for that layer:
they are not an AI-augmented, two-person-team
runtime. A centaur unit should read OBAF-style
artifacts primarily as [1m[1;37mupstream intent and[0m
[1m[1;37mcoordination constraints[0m â€” a way to stay aligned
with a broader north-star â€” without importing
heavyweight planning/ceremony into a context where
coordination cost is already negligible.

If you are only a single small unit, the Centaur
kernel below is usually sufficient. If you become
many units with real dependencies, add the minimal
composition rules in this manifest (see [1m[1;37mScaling[0m
[1m[1;37mand composition[0m) and let the org-level layer do
what it is good at: outcome portfolio coherence.

[1;34m## [0m[1;34mThe model[0m

A centaur unit is a [1m[1;37msmall team[0m (often 2â€“4 humans)
operating with AI augmentation. The unit is
defined less by headcount than by a capability
mix:

[36m-[0m [1m[1;37mDomain expertise[0m holds the truth about what
  matters, why it matters, who it matters to, and
  how to know if it changed.
[36m-[0m [1m[1;37mBuilding expertise[0m holds the truth about how
  change is made real: systems design,
  integration, reliability, security, operability,
  and proof.

A centaur unit may be one domain expert with one
builder, one domain expert with multiple builders,
or a builder with deep domain adjacency. The unit
remains [3m[34m"centaur"[0m so long as intent is explicit,
constraints are enforced, and evidence governs
direction.

AI is treated as an accelerator of execution and
exploration, not as an authority. Human judgment
remains responsible for intent, constraints, and
proof.

[1;34m## [0m[1;34mThe tenets[0m

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m1) Outcomes over outputs[0m

Outputs are deliverables; outcomes are observable
changes in the world.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m2) Evidence is the arbiter[0m

Plans are hypotheses. Confidence yields to
signals, observation, and reproducible checks.
Signals are [3m[34mlearning instruments[0m, not performance
targets. When a signal becomes a target, it
becomes easier to game and less useful as
evidence.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m3) Constraints are first-class[0m

Security, reliability, cost, compliance,
operability, and interfaces/contracts (boundaries
over heroics) are part of the outcome, not
deferred work.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m4) Verification dominates execution[0m

When generation is cheap, proof becomes the
bottleneck. Design work so correctness is
continuously demonstrable.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m5) Automation-first governance[0m

Policies live in pipelines and checks, not in
meetings and approvals. Automation must remain
[3m[34menabling[0m, not controlling. Automate constraints
and proof, not politics.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m6) Micro-iterations, small batches[0m

Short cycles reduce error, maximize learning rate,
and limit blast radius.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m7) One source of truth for intent[0m

A canonical intent artifact defines why, what
success means, and what must not break.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m8) Coordination is artifact-driven[0m

Async by default. Sync time is reserved for
irreducible human alignment. Ownership follows
capability and accountability, not titles.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m9) Maintain conceptual integrity under speed[0m

Protect shared mental models. Prevent drift as
change velocity rises.

[1;35m### [0m[1;35m10) Capture learning while cheap[0m

Reflection is mandatory, lightweight, and tied to
events. Surprises must improve future work.

